{
  "text": "This equation models light transport in a heterogeneous translucent medium [CITATION_1] , i.e. V q is the fraction of light along the ray that is absorbed by Gaussian G q . The original paper [CITATION_2] describes an analytic approximation to Equation 3 by sampling the outer integral. Different to their work, we apply this ray casting model to infer the visibility of the background, B(o, n) = 1− q V q (o, n). Assuming that the background is infinitely distant, B is the fraction of light not absorbed by the Gaussian model:",
